11 § 4633. FARM SECURITY SPECIAL FUND; GRANTS
12 (a) The Secretary, after consultation with the Review Board, shall award
13 grants from the Farm Security Special Fund to farms that have incurred
14 financial losses or expenses due to an eligible weather condition.
15 (1) Grants from the fund shall be in an amount that reimburses a farm
16 for up to 50 percent of uninsured or otherwise uncovered losses due to eligible
17 weather conditions, up to a maximum award of $150,000.00 total per year per
18 qualified applicant farm.
19 (2) The Secretary shall establish criteria for the amount of an award
20 based on the annual net income of the farm in relation to the median net
21 income of all farms in Vermont.
